<font color="#FF0000">DEATH OF A SITE.</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  8 12:48:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I jsut stumbled across this site today.  Offered some thoughts on my  first visit to the Wall.  Then I came across this topic.  What hell is going on.  It this site shutting down?<br><br>
Jesus Christ!  Don't do it.  This seems like one of the relatively sane places for people to interact on a topic that has ripped out the heart of an entire generation.<br><br>
I was just thinking about my comments regading the Wall.  I wondered if my friends who are etched in stone have families who might want to talk with someone who was with their sons, brothers, uncles, etc., who never got the straight story about what happened.  Was going to send you that suggestion, that you figure out a way to link a guy's name to a registration book of some sort.  People don't surf the names just to surf.  They want to find their friend or loved one who never came home alive.  We are the only ones who can offer a little more information to them, and we don't even know who they are.<br><br>
It would also be a way for other friends who we've lost contact with to find each other.<br><br>
Don't know what the plans are, but let's find a way to keep this site alive!<br><br>
Maybe we can get Senator Kerry (medal of honor winner) from Kansas to initiate a bill so that Newt's fine for being a crook go to the support of this site.  Someone please tell me what's going on here...?<br><br>
Jim Morse<br>
